OL,6,FThe accountants, Mr Henderson and Mr
OL,7,FWarmington, presented a damning
OL,8,Fassessment of in its investigations
OL,9,Fand prosecutions of sub-postmasters.
OL,11,FHundreds of innocent people were
OL,12,Fconvicted. They found they were denied
OL,13,Fthe right to defend themselves and
OL,14,Fforced into "courtroom step deals"
OL,15,Fwith little choice but to plead guilty.
OL,17,FAlso facing questions during
OL,18,FWednesday's session is Susan Crichton,
OL,19,Fanother former general counsel to the
